The paper deals with learning a sparse model from large-scale and high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of sparsity-inducing regularizers and $\ell_1$-norm regularization suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
